@DomT4 

> I'm reluctant to encourage more environment variables based on the feedback we've had that people loathe having to find them.

It's not only a problem of people loathing to find them; more env vars have practical consequences. All env vars count toward `ARG_MAX` which is 262144 at the moment, so you can only have a finite number of them, and as you add more of them to your environment you have less space for `argv`, which means shorten command lines, more instances spawned by `xargs`, and so on.

